Date: Sun 29 Mar 2020
Source: Nigeria Center for Disease Control (NCDC) [edited]
https://ncdc.gov.ng/diseases/sitreps/?cat=5&name=An%20update%20of%20Lassa%20fever%20outbreak%20in%20Nigeria


Lassa fever situation report -- epidemiological week 13 (23-29 Mar 2020)
------------------------------------------------------------------
Key points
----------
Table 1: Summary of current week (13), cumulative from epiweeks 1-13, 2020, and comparison with previous year (2019)
Current week (13) [23-29 Mar 2020) / Cumulative weeks 1-13 / Cumulative 2019 weeks 1-13
Suspected cases: 182 / 4194 / 2034
Confirmed cases: 19 / 951/ 526
Probable cases: 0 / 14 / 15
Deaths: 1 / 185 / 121
Case fatality rate (CFR [%]): 5.3 / 19.5 / 23.0
Number of states affected: 8 / 27 / 21
Local government areas (LGAs) affected: 14 / 126 / 74

Highlights

- In week 13, the number of new confirmed cases decreased from 28 cases in week 12, 2020, to 19 cases. These were reported from 8 states (Edo, Ondo, Ebonyi, Bauchi, Taraba, Plateau, Kogi, and Delta) (table 3).
- Cumulatively from week 1 to week 13, 2020, 185 deaths have been reported, with a case fatality rate (CFR) of 19.5%, which is lower than the CFR for the same period in 2019 (23.0%).
- In total for 2020, 27 states have recorded at least one confirmed case across 126 local government areas [LGAs] (figures 2 and 3).
- Of all confirmed cases, 72% are from Edo (32%), Ondo (32%), and Ebonyi (8%) states.
- The predominant age group affected is 21-30 years (range: less than 1 to 78 years; median age: 33 years). The male-to-female ratio for confirmed cases is 1:1.2 (figure 4).
- The number of suspected cases has significantly increased compared to that reported for the same period in 2019.
- No new healthcare worker was affected in the reporting week 13.

